The All Progressives Congress (APC) has postponed its special convention for the presidential primary from Sunday, 29th – Monday, 30th of May, 2020 to Monday, 6th – Wednesday, 8th of June, 2022. APC’s National Publicity Secretary, Mr Felix Morka explained that the decision was in line with the Independent National Electoral Commission’s (INEC) extension of the deadline for the submission of the list of candidates by political parties. Details later.